Class ResultManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagSupport
      • com.sprhibrad.framework.tags.ShrTagSupport
        • com.sprhibrad.framework.tags.FormAccessor
          • com.sprhibrad.framework.tags.ListManagerAccessor
            • com.sprhibrad.framework.tags.ResultManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataSetManager, IteratorDataSetManager, java.io.Serializable, javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.IterationTag, javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.JspTag, javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.Tag

    public class ResultManager
extends ListManagerAccessor
implements IteratorDataSetManager
    Acquires, as tag attributes, the fields to be rendered, the default orientation for sorting and the set of row actions. All the attributes that concur to the dbms inquiry, here can be picked up as tag attributes because the first time the hosting jsp is rendered, the inquiry is still to be launched (that occurs when the search/list page is requested because the navigation came to the entity to inspect the chances to compose the filter (iteration = -1).
